HEADWORD: Pauline
<hw>Pau"line</hw> <pr>(p⟦add⟧"l⟦imac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Paulinus</ets>, fr. <ets>Paulus</ets> Paul.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to the apostle <persfn>Paul</persfn>, or his writings;
resembling, or conforming to, the writings of <persfn>Paul</persfn>;
<as>as, the <ex>Pauline</ex> epistles; <ex>Pauline</ex>
doctrine.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My religion had always been <qex>Pauline</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>J. H.
Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paulist</ent>⟦br⟧
